---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ProjectGrid from '../../components/ProjectGrid.astro';
import { navigation, profile, ui } from '../../data/site';

const locale = 'en';
---
<BaseLayout title="Ann / 林庭安 — Woodwork Portfolio" description={profile.headline[locale]} locale={locale} alternatePath="/zh-TW">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero__copy">
      <p class="eyebrow">{profile.intro[locale]}</p>
      <h1>{profile.headline[locale]}</h1>
      <p>{profile.bio[locale]}</p>
      <div class="hero__actions">
        <a class="button" href="#work">{navigation[locale].work}</a>
        <a class="button button--ghost" href={profile.pdfPath}>Workshop PDF</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <figure class="hero__image">
      <img src={profile.heroImage} alt="Ann working with wood in a workshop" />
    </figure>
  </section>
  <section class="section story-section" id="story">
    <p class="eyebrow">{navigation[locale].story}</p>
    <h2>{ui.storyTitle[locale]}</h2>
    <p>Ann’s strongest professional thread is transformation: spaces into drawings, raw timber into objects, discarded material into new value. This portfolio turns the workshop presentation into a living CV with project evidence instead of a static document.</p>
  </section>
  <ProjectGrid locale={locale} />
  <section class="section process-section" id="process">
    <p class="eyebrow">{navigation[locale].process}</p>
    <h2>{ui.processTitle[locale]}</h2>
    <div class="process-grid">
      <p>Interior design gives Ann composition, proportion, and site awareness. Woodworking adds tolerance, material behavior, and the discipline of making ideas physically true.</p>
      <p>The next step is deeper evidence: more process photos, material notes, and before/after documentation for restoration and reclaimed wood projects.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <footer class="contact-section" id="contact">
    <p class="eyebrow">{ui.contactTitle[locale]}</p>
    <a href={`mailto:${profile.email}`}>{profile.email}</a>
  </footer>
</BaseLayout>
